                <h1>What Does a Crack Pipe Look Like? Understanding Its Characteristics</h1>
                <p>A crack pipe typically appears as a small, cylindrical tube made from glass or metal, often with a bulbous end to hold the drug. They are commonly around 4 to 6 inches in length and may have a jagged stem or be straight. Signs of use can include residue, burns, or discoloration on the pipe's surface, indicating previous substance use.</p>
